(1 comment)
are we downloading the license file from with in bmcweb? can't we pass the file url to demon and let demon do the file downloading from client?
bmcweb calls Download D-bus service

This change is associated with a request on openbmc/technical-oversight-forum. Please see the following link for additional discussion:

https://github.com/openbmc/technical-oversight-forum/issues/28
I suspect most or all of these properties are expected to be "readonly".  Please add the appropriate flag(s).
yes, most of these properties populated while creating license and can't be changed later.

Is this intended to be used by human-oriented user interfaces or is there some programmatic interpretation of this string?  If there is not any programmatic interpretation, please document.  I'd like to see language matching many other interfaces: see `$ git grep programmatic`.
intent of this Name property is to populate license name like Processor,Memory etc.,
Done
Do we need any information about the issuing entity?  For instance, could Oracle issue a license for an IBM machine?
I think it may be needed, will get back to you on this.

https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/License.v1_1_1.json , already have property "manufacturer"  "The manufacturer or producer of this license.". for this.

Ravi,
Seeing some of the enums are not matched with license service definition.

Jayanth

Yes, I did not add D-bus properties for all redfish properties.
this commit adds D-bus properties which are required to represent common licenses
intent was to add other properties on need basis.
I will add D-bus properties for manufacturer details
Done
Please follow Time.EpochTime and use microseconds.
Done
size
Done
This seems to only be applicable to the "Capacity" type?  Please document.
Done
What is a prototype-license?
license that is designed for the development or internal use.
Done
How is the restriction identified as to which device this is authorized for?

AuthorizedDevices can be listed as Links

 License_v1_1_1_Links:
      additionalProperties: false
      description: The links to other resources that are related to this resource.
      properties:
        AuthorizedDevices:
          description: An array of links to the devices authorized by the license.
Done
Probably isn't any reason to add "License" on the end here, as this is already "License.Install" from an interface perspective.  'install' would be sufficient.
Done
Generally we're moving away from file paths and towards an open fd being passed to the daemon.
ok but in this case D-bus app needs file path to download license file from client using TFTP
Can we please name this interface accordingly then, e.g. `TFTPInstall`? Or separate out the method of acquisition from the act of installing the license?

TFTP is one of transfer protocol used for getting the license file on BMC.
this method defined for installing new license.
Then we can use file descriptors like Patrick suggested, right? Because TFTP is a separate concern?

Hi Andrew 

sure, got it. modified to use file descriptor.
thinking again its better to use "xyz.openbmc_project.Software.Download" to download license file to BMC to specified path, so bmcweb can directly call this D-bus with given file URI to download this file to BMC filesystem and bmcweb can share this file fd to license manager manager while installing license
okay, if we have some agreement on passing file descriptors can you please update the interface spec here?
Oh, never mind, I see that you have, I was looking at the wrong revision 😄
I'm not sure "Generally" is true here? Maybe "Some"?

yes I agree its not general for all other servers..
it applies to some of server systems
Why are we exposing these on DBus though? How are the interfaces to be consumed? Please put the answer and any relevant links into the commit message.

These D-bus interfaces will be consumed in redfish license service implementation.
updated commit message
who is responsible to provide this file descriptor?
BMCWEB call this license install menthod with fd of given license file
This means BmcWeb downloads file from the client. Is that correct?
yes, bmcweb calls "xyz.openbmc_project.Software.Download" based on transfer protocol type
Ack. Seems like this needs to be updated in the design document.
